desktop-defaults (0.8.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Take control of all kde defaults for live user.
    - keep large template rc files in /usr/share/desktop-defaults-kde/
    - disable select apps in fll-kde-desktop.init
    - create and populate .kde/share/config of live user in fll-kde-desktop.init
  * Fix for loop that populated live user with rc template files.
  * Disable arts when no sound device is present/supported.
  * Special handling of kpowersaverc. Disable kcmlaptop when kpowersave is
    installed.
  * Add konsolerc handling to fll-kde-desktop.init. Remove template konsolerc.
  * Standardize fll-*-desktop.init output.
  * Attempt to address the percieved font problem in a more intelligent and
    flexible way than just throwing personalised files into /etc/skel.

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Mon, 04 Jun 2007 21:28:51 +1000

